TITLE: Filtering Analytics by Tags with Dub API in Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to filter analytics data by tags. It initializes the Dub client and makes an API request to retrieve click data for links with specific tag IDs over a 30-day period, allowing for more targeted analytics.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dubinc/docs/blob/main/concepts/analytics.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Dub } from "dub";

export const dub = new Dub({
  token: process.env.DUB_API_KEY,
});

const result = await dub.analytics.retrieve({
  event: "clicks",
  groupBy: "top_links",
  tagIds: ["tag_12345", "tag_67890"],
  interval: "30d",
});
```

