TITLE: Tracking Sale Events with Dub SDK in Ruby
DESCRIPTION: Example of tracking sale events using the Dub SDK in Ruby. The code initializes the Dub client with an API key from environment variables, creates a TrackSaleRequest object with sale details, and makes a sale tracking call.
SOURCE: https://github.com/dubinc/docs/blob/main/conversions/sales/introduction.mdx#2025-04-10_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: ruby
CODE:
```
require 'dub'

dub = ::OpenApiSDK::Dub.new
dub.config_security(
  ::OpenApiSDK::Shared::Security.new(
    token: ENV['DUB_API_KEY']
  )
)

req = ::OpenApiSDK::Operations::TrackSaleRequest.new(
  external_id: 'cus_RBfbD57HDzPKpduI8elr5qHA',
  amount: 100,
  payment_processor: 'stripe',
  event_name: 'E-book purchase',
  invoice_id: '123456',
  currency: 'usd'
)

dub.track.sale(req)
```

